The paper focuses on incorporating semantic priors into a deep reinforcement learning framework for visual navigation. This involves using graph convolutional networks to incorporate prior knowledge into the agent's decision-making process. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves robotics (cs.RO) as it uses the AI2-THOR framework for evaluation. Finally, natural language processing (cs.CL) may also be a relevant sub-category as the paper deals with incorporating semantic knowledge into the navigation task.
